gistrate, Mrs. S. K. Matepo admitted the accused to a bail of N50,000 each with one surety in like sum. Matepo adjourned the case till Jan. 29, for mention. vanguard Gbadebo, of no fixed address, is being tried for intent to commit felony and stealing. Earlier, the prosecutor, Insp. George Nwosu, told the court that the accused committed the offences on Aug. 7 at No. 2, Adeosun St., Oko-Oba, Abule-Egba, Lagos. He said that the accused unlawfully entered the shop of one… August 16, 2016 In "News" Two friends who allegedly stole a car valued at N2 million were brought before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court on Friday. September 14, 2018 In "News" A 25-year-old tricycle rider, Oluwole Odebo, who allegedly stole his passenger ‘s mobile phones valued at N200,000, on Wednesday appeared before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court. March 28, 2018 In "News"